cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses strategies to improve the scalability of parallel applications running on large-scale systems.
- cs.PF (Performance) is also likely as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on a supercomputer.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses a dataflow processing paradigm among groups of processes.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach to constructing parallel applications.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper provides a proof-of-concept implementation using MPI.
